# Cursor Rules Index

## Purpose

This index provides a quick reference to all cursor rules, their purposes, and when they apply.

## Core Rules (Always Apply)

### Universal Behavior
- **`general.mdc`** - Universal behavior, file management, and rule hierarchy
  - Base rules that apply to all tasks
  - References to specialized rules
  - Conflict resolution guidance

### Documentation Structure
- **`00_core_instructions.mdc`** - Document structure and templates
  - PRD, RFP, Tender Response, Architecture Design, Solution Proposal templates
  - Universal document structure requirements
  - Document-specific rules and validation

### Context Management
- **`01_session_ledger.mdc`** - **MANDATORY** session ledger updates
  - Tracks all AI interactions and context across sessions
  - Required after every user request
  - Format and best practices

### Writing Standards
- **`writing_style_and_tone.mdc`** - Writing style, tone, and formatting
  - Professional writing principles
  - Prohibited elements (formatting, language)
  - Code comment standards
  - Audience adaptation

### File Management
- **`file_management.mdc`** - File creation and organization
  - File creation principles
  - Documentation location rules
  - Temporary file guidelines

## Specialized Rules (Apply When Relevant)

### Code Development
- **`02_coding_behavior.mdc`** - Code modification principles
  - Before/after change workflows
  - Code modification best practices
  - File management for code

- **`03_documentation.mdc`** - Code documentation standards
  - Function docstring requirements
  - Code comment standards
  - Documentation requirements

- **`04_coding_mode.mdc`** - Language-specific and cloud patterns
  - Python, .NET, TypeScript/JavaScript guidelines
  - Cloud architecture patterns
  - Testing requirements
  - Code review checklist

### Documentation Types
- **`05_how_to.mdc`** - How-to documentation for users
  - Non-technical user guides
  - Step-by-step instructions
  - Converting technical content to user guides

### Quality and Consistency
- **`accuracy_and_verification.mdc`** - Factuality requirements
  - Verify technical claims
  - No hallucinations
  - Real citations only

- **`consistency_and_reuse.mdc`** - Terminology and templates
  - Consistent terminology
  - Template reuse
  - Alignment with style guides

- **`communication_and_collaboration.mdc`** - Collaboration guidelines
  - Handling uncertainty
  - Summarizing complex topics
  - Handoff procedures

### Architecture
- **`strict_architecture_governance.mdc`** - Architectural governance
  - Architecture principles
  - Change control
  - Documentation requirements
  - Risk and threat modeling

## Rule Hierarchy

1. **`general.mdc`** - Base rules (always apply)
2. **Specialized rules** - Apply when relevant to task domain
3. **Conflict resolution**:
   - General rules override specialized rules for tone, clarity, and safety
   - Specialized rules override general rules for domain-specific structure or compliance

## Quick Reference

| Task Type | Primary Rules |
|-----------|--------------|
| Writing documentation | `general.mdc`, `writing_style_and_tone.mdc`, `00_core_instructions.mdc` |
| Writing code | `general.mdc`, `02_coding_behavior.mdc`, `03_documentation.mdc`, `04_coding_mode.mdc` |
| Architecture design | `general.mdc`, `strict_architecture_governance.mdc`, `00_core_instructions.mdc` |
| User guides | `general.mdc`, `05_how_to.mdc`, `writing_style_and_tone.mdc` |
| Any task | `general.mdc`, `01_session_ledger.mdc` (mandatory) |

## Notes

- All rules marked with `alwaysApply: true` are automatically applied
- Rules marked with `alwaysApply: false` require explicit reference
- When in doubt, check `general.mdc` for base behavior
- Session ledger updates are mandatory after every user request
